This folder contains dd.dtd that specifies the syntax of appmanager
application download descriptors, usually found at
src/appmanager/repository/apps/<application_name>/par/oma/.

To refer to the dtd from a dd file, insert the following after the xml
declaration (<?xml> tag):

<!DOCTYPE media PUBLIC
    "-//Sun Microsystems//CDC AMS Download Descriptor//EN" "dd.dtd">

This sample refers to the dd.dtd in the same directory. The dd.dtd could be
specified using either global or local path. Considering the .dtd file is at
src/appmanager/repository/, and application's xml is under
src/appmanager/repository/apps/<application_name>/par/oma/,
the local reference will be ../../../../ota/dd.dtd

The Download Descriptors should pass validation when checked against
this DTD.
